tourBios.otherInfo: Member of the Nationwide Tour in 2001...Made the cut in two of three Nationwide Tour starts in 2003...Fired a second-round 63 to take the 36-hole lead at the Alberta Calgary Classic in August. Struggled on the weekend, with rounds of 73-71 that dropped him to a T31...Three weeks later, was tied for ninth after 36 holes at the Albertsons Boise Open. Added rounds of 71-69 to wind up T11, his best finish in 29 career starts on the Nationwide Tour. Member of the Canadian Tour for six years. Made the cut in 14 of 24 starts over the past two years, with his best finish a T4 at the 2002 MTS Classic...Played in five PGA TOUR events in his career but failed to make a cut...Was the 1993 and 1994 Big 8 Conference champion, as well as an All-America selection in those two years...Has one hole-in-one during competition...Brother of Nationwide Tour member Tom Kalinowski.

tourBios.curYrHigh: T65 at the 2013 Dakota Dunes Open
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Named an All- American at Colorado in 1993 and 1994, and was the Big Eight Conference champion those same years.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the PGA TOUR Canada was T14th in 2011 at the Times Colonist Island Savings Open.
